## Phase 6: Database, Real-Time & Core Backend

### Objective

Design and implement the complete Supabase PostgreSQL schema with Row-Level Security policies, all real-time subscriptions for live tracking and request updates, Supabase Edge Functions for the donor matching algorithm, push notification dispatch, donation cooldown management, and PDF certificate generation.

***

### Task 6.1 – Database Schema Design

**Step 1:** Create the following tables in Supabase via SQL migrations:

**`profiles` table:**

```sql
CREATE TABLE profiles (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE UNIQUE,
  full_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  phone TEXT,
  role TEXT CHECK (role IN ('donor', 'requester', 'hospital_staff', 'admin')),
  blood_group TEXT CHECK (blood_group IN ('A+','A-','B+','B-','AB+','AB-','O+','O-')),
  dob DATE,
  gender TEXT,
  city TEXT,
  location JSONB,  -- { lat, lng }
  avatar_url TEXT,
  emergency_contact_name TEXT,
  emergency_contact_phone TEXT,
  availability_status TEXT DEFAULT 'available' 
    CHECK (availability_status IN ('available','unavailable','traveling','on_cooldown')),
  notification_preference TEXT DEFAULT 'both',
  alert_radius_km INTEGER DEFAULT 10,
  setup_complete BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  last_donation_date TIMESTAMPTZ,
  cooldown_ends_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  total_donations INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  sms_enabled BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
  push_enabled BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
  quiet_hours_start TIME,
  quiet_hours_end TIME,
  referral_code TEXT UNIQUE DEFAULT LEFT(gen_random_uuid()::TEXT, 8),
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

**`blood_requests` table:**

```sql
CREATE TABLE blood_requests (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  requester_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
  blood_group TEXT NOT NULL,
  units_needed INTEGER NOT NULL,
  urgency_level TEXT CHECK (urgency_level IN ('critical','moderate','routine')),
  hospital_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  hospital_location JSONB NOT NULL,  -- { lat, lng, address }
  hospital_id UUID REFERENCES hospitals(id),
  patient_name TEXT,
  notes TEXT,
  contact_phone TEXT,
  radius_km INTEGER DEFAULT 10,
  sms_mode_enabled BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  status TEXT DEFAULT 'searching' 
    CHECK (status IN ('searching','donor_found','en_route','completed','cancelled')),
  donors_pinged INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  accepted_donor_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  closed_at TIMESTAMPTZ
);
```

**`donor_pings` table:**

```sql
CREATE TABLE donor_pings (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  request_id UUID REFERENCES blood_requests(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  donor_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
  status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending' 
    CHECK (status IN ('pending','accepted','declined','snoozed','expired')),
  decline_reason TEXT,
  notified_via TEXT,  -- 'push' | 'sms' | 'both'
  pinged_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  responded_at TIMESTAMPTZ
);
```

**`donations` table:**

```sql
CREATE TABLE donations (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  request_id UUID REFERENCES blood_requests(id),
