### Task 6.2 – Row-Level Security (RLS) Policies

**Step 1:** Enable RLS on all tables:

```sql
ALTER TABLE profiles ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE blood_requests ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE donor_pings ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE donations ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE notifications ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE donor_tracking ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
```

**Step 2:** Define RLS policies:

`profiles`:

* SELECT: authenticated users can read their own profile; donors can read basic info of other donors (limited columns via view)
* INSERT: user can only insert their own profile (`user_id = auth.uid()`)
* UPDATE: user can only update their own profile

`blood_requests`:

* SELECT: authenticated users can read all non-cancelled requests
* INSERT: authenticated requesters and hospital staff can insert
* UPDATE: requester can update their own requests; admin can update all

`notifications`:

* SELECT, UPDATE: user can only see/update their own notifications

`donor_pings`:

* SELECT: donor can see their own pings; requester can see pings for their requests

`donor_tracking`:

* SELECT: requester of the related request can read; donor can update their own

**Step 3:** Create a restricted view `public_donor_profiles` that exposes only non-sensitive fields (name initials, blood group, city, availability — no phone, no exact location) for hospital staff searches.

